gy and histology, and potentially mediastinoscopy if indicated by imaging.  This will allow for definitive diagnosis and staging of the disease, which is crucial for determining appropriate treatment options.  A multidisciplinary team (MDT) meeting involving oncology, radiology, pathology, and potentially thoracic surgery is crucial for optimal patient management.  Given the comorbidities, careful consideration of treatment toxicity and potential interactions between cancer therapies and existing medications is paramount.\n\n\n**Conclusion:**\n\nThis patient requires immediate specialist referral for suspected lung cancer.  The patient's comorbidities will need to be carefully considered when developing a treatment plan.  A multidisciplinary approach is essential for optimizing patient care and achieving the best possible outcome.",
